d resistance in the face of appropriation and occupation, while in Japan it nurtures a merged Japanese-Hawaiian artistic and cultural sensibility. For diasporic Hawaiians in California, it provides a way to claim Hawaiian identity. By demonstrating how slack key guitar is a site for the articulation of Hawaiian values, Fellezs illuminates how slack key guitarists are reconfiguring notions of Hawaiian belonging, aesthetics, and politics throughout the transPacific.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aGuitar music (Slack key)zCaliforniaxHistory and criticism. 0aGuitar music (Slack key)zCalifornia. 0aGuitar music (Slack key)zHawaiixHistory and criticism. 0aGuitar music (Slack key)zHawaii. 0aGuitar music (Slack key)zJapanxHistory and criticism. 0aGuitar music (Slack key)zJapan. 0aGuitar music (Slack key)zPacific AreaxHistory and criticism. 0aGuitar music (Slack key)zPacific Area. 0aHawaiian guitar musiczCaliforniaxHistory and criticism. 0aHawaiian guitar musiczCalifornia. 0aHawaiian guitar musiczHawaiixHistory and criticism. 0aHawaiian guitar musiczHawaii. 0aHawaiian guitar musiczJapanxHistory and criticism. 0aHawaiian guitar musiczJapan. 0aHawaiian guitar musiczPacific AreaxHistory and criticism. 0aHawaiian guitar musiczPacific Area. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478007418zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478007418423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478007418.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles